        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 1:00PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 100 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
North-South Lake Campground, or 7 miles northwest of Catskill, moving
northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hudson, Catskill, Chatham, Nassau, New Baltimore, Stephentown,
Coxsackie, New Lebanon, Valatie, Athens, Kinderhook, Lorenz Park,
North-South Lake Campground, Coeymans, Cairo, Ghent, Stockport,
Stuyvesant, Canaan, and East Nassau.

This includes Interstate 87 between exits 21 and 21B.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
